,"senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to weaken","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to weaken, to make weak","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to double","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to geminate (a consonant)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَعُفَ (ḍaʕufa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weakness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of ضَعُفَ (ḍaʕufa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"weakness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"double"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a multiple, (after numerals) -fold","examples":[{"text":"وَمَثَلُ ٱلَّذِینَ یُنفِقُونَ أَمۡوَ ٰ⁠لَهُمُ ٱبۡتِغَاۤءَ مَرۡضَاتِ ٱللَّهِ وَتَثۡبِیتࣰا مِّنۡ أَنفُسِهِمۡ كَمَثَلِ جَنَّةِۭ بِرَبۡوَةٍ أَصَابَهَا وَابِلࣱ فَـَٔاتَتۡ أُكُلَهَا ضِعۡفَیۡنِ فَإِن لَّمۡ یُصِبۡهَا وَابِلࣱ فَطَلࣱّۗ وَٱللَّهُ بِمَا تَعۡمَلُونَ بَصِیرٌ","english":"And the example of those who donate their wealth, seeking Allah’s pleasure and believing the reward is certain,1 is that of a garden on a fertile hill: when heavy rain falls, it yields up twice its normal produce. If no heavy rain falls, a drizzle is sufficient. And Allah is All-Seeing of what you do. — Translated by Dr. Mustafa Khattab, The Clear Quran"},{"text":"إِلاَّ نالَ الآنَ في هٰذهِ الدُّنْيا مائةَ ضِعْفٍ مِنَ البُيوتِ والإِخوَةِ والأَخَواتِ والأُمَّهاتِ والبَنينَ والحُقولِ مع الاِضطِهادات، ونالَ في الآخِرَةِ الحَياةَ الأَبَدِيَّة.","english":"who will not receive one hundred times as much, now in this time: houses, and brothers, and sisters, and mothers, and children, and land, with persecutions, and in the future age eternal life."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null}